  <h2>
    Basic Information On Submitting a Proposed NSRR Project to Your Local IRB
  </h2>
</div>


<p class="lead-paragraph">
  We are required to obtain evidence that your project/purpose has been <strong><i><u>reviewed</u></i></strong> by your local IRB/Ethics Committee. Most local IRB reviews will likely result in a <u>Determination Letter</u> stating the proposed research/project is exempt due to:
</p>

<p class="lead-paragraph">
  <ul>
    <li>not meeting the criteria/definition of Human Subject Research; and</li>
    <li>no direct or indirect contact with an individual or interpersonal contact with an individual; and</li>
    <li>the information obtained from the activity cannot be linked, or associated to a particular individual, and</li>
    <li>the identity of the person may not be ascertained by the investigator under 45 CFR46 or 21 CFR 56.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<p class="lead-paragraph">
