</p>

<p class="lead-paragraph">
  The National Sleep Research Resource (NSRR) site is a comprehensive easily accessible, well-annotated national repository of de-identified sleep data, including bio-physiological signals, which are linked to risk factor and outcome data for participants in major National Institute of Health studies. Also available to the research community on the site are data integration and signal processing tools. (<%= link_to SITE_URL, SITE_URL %>)
  If your submission results in a letter or memo from the IRB/Ethics Committee stating they determined this is not human research and does not require further IRB review, we will accept that letter/memo. Attach that document to the signed DAUA and access will be approved.
  Based on the details of your project and local IRB rules and procedures, your submission may result in a full IRB review and that approval letter would be attached to the DAUA.
</p>
